---
const slots = Array.from({ length: 5 });
---

<section class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-5 py-16 sm:px-8">
  <div class="mb-10 max-w-3xl">
    <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-cyan-200" data-i18n="memes.eyebrow">
      Visual proof
    </p>
    <h2 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-black tracking-tight text-white sm:text-5xl" data-i18n="memes.title">
      The problem is not access to AI. It is control.
    </h2>
  </div>

  <div class="grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-5">
    {
      slots.map((_, index) => (
        <article class="glass-card rounded-[1.75rem] p-5">
          <div class="mb-5 flex aspect-video items-center justify-center rounded-[1.25rem] border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/70 p-4 text-center">
            <p class="text-sm font-black uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-cyan-100" data-i18n={`memes.items.${index}.0`}>
              Access is not enough
            </p>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white" data-i18n={`memes.items.${index}.0`}>
            Access is not enough
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300" data-i18n={`memes.items.${index}.1`}>
            Without structure, AI creates chaos. With control, it creates useful executive output.
          </p>
        </article>
      ))
    }
  </div>
</section>
